      • segments

        public static List<List<String>> segments(List<String> responseLines,
                                          List<String> markers)
        separates response lines into segments.

        A list of response lines may be repeated. For example, a list of songs is a repeated list of responses. The fields are repeated while the values can be different. These repeated lines can be divided into separate lists. This is useful to process each segment individually as independent lists of string for parsing.

        When calling this method, we hope we have identified the correct label of the first line of each possible segment. The MPD protocol is not suited for this. The protocol does not use definitive separators. We make the following assumptions:

        • The order of fields is deterministic within a given MPD instance.
        • The MPD server implementation doesn't change much.
        • The MPD server source code is open to inspection.
        • The MPD server's implementation can verified by observation with a tool such as netcap.

        Parameters:
        responseLines - to search
        markers - that identify the first line of each segment
        Returns:
        list of identified segments in 'responseLines'
